# SkillBridge Backend üéì

**REST API for Tutor Booking Platform**

This repository contains the backend API for **SkillBridge**, a tutoring platform that connects students with tutors.
It is built using **Node.js, Express.js, and Prisma ORM** and provides authentication, role-based access control, booking management, and admin moderation features.

---

## üöÄ Project Overview

The backend handles:

* User authentication and authorization
* Tutor profile and availability management
* Booking and review system
* Admin management of users and categories

It serves as the core business logic layer for the SkillBridge frontend (Next.js).

---

## üõ† Tech Stack

* **Node.js** ‚Äì JavaScript runtime
* **Express.js** ‚Äì REST API framework
* **Prisma ORM** ‚Äì Database ORM
* **PostgreSQL** ‚Äì Database (via Prisma)
* **Better Auth** ‚Äì Secure login
* **bcrypt** ‚Äì Password hashing
* **dotenv** ‚Äì Environment configuration

---

## üîê Authentication & Authorization

* JWT-based authentication
* Role-based access control: **Student, Tutor, Admin**
* Protected routes using middleware
* Admin users must be seeded manually

---

## üë• Roles & Permissions

| Role    | Permissions                                        |
| ------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Student | Book sessions, view bookings, leave reviews        |
| Tutor   | Create profile, manage availability, view sessions |
| Admin   | Manage users, categories, and bookings             |

---

## ‚ú® Features

* User registration and login
* Tutor browsing and filtering
* Booking system with status management
* Review and rating system
* Admin panel support
* Category management
* Secure API with validation and middleware

---

## üóÑ Database Models

Main entities:

* **User**
* **TutorProfile**
* **Category**
* **Booking**
* **Review**

> Designed using Prisma schema with proper relations.

---

## üîå API Endpoints

### Auth

| Method | Endpoint             | Description        |
| ------ | -------------------- | ------------------ |
| POST   | `/api/auth/register` | Register user      |
| POST   | `/api/auth/login`    | Login user         |
| GET    | `/api/auth/me`       | Get logged-in user |

---

### Tutors (Public)

| Method | Endpoint          | Description        |
| ------ | ----------------- | ------------------ |
| GET    | `/api/tutors`     | Get all tutors     |
| GET    | `/api/tutors/:id` | Get tutor by ID    |
| GET    | `/api/categories` | Get all categories |

---

### Bookings

| Method | Endpoint            | Description         |
| ------ | ------------------- | ------------------- |
| POST   | `/api/bookings`     | Create booking      |
| GET    | `/api/bookings`     | Get user bookings   |
| GET    | `/api/bookings/:id` | Get booking details |

---

### Tutor Management

| Method | Endpoint                  | Description          |
| ------ | ------------------------- | -------------------- |
| PUT    | `/api/tutor/profile`      | Update tutor profile |
| PUT    | `/api/tutor/availability` | Update availability  |

---

### Reviews

| Method | Endpoint       | Description   |
| ------ | -------------- | ------------- |
| POST   | `/api/reviews` | Create review |

---

### Admin

| Method | Endpoint                | Description      |
| ------ | ----------------------- | ---------------- |
| GET    | `/api/admin/users`      | Get all users    |
| PATCH  | `/api/admin/users/:id`  | Ban / unban user |
| GET    | `/api/admin/bookings`   | Get all bookings |
| POST   | `/api/admin/categories` | Create category  |

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Installation & Setup

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/skillbridge-backend.git
cd skillbridge-backend
```

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Setup environment variables


### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Run database migrations

```bash
npx prisma migrate dev
```

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Generate Prisma client

```bash
npx prisma generate
```

---

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Start the server

```bash
npm run dev
```

Server will run on:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

## üß™ Scripts

```bash
npm run dev      # Start in development mode
npm start        # Start in production
npx prisma studio # Open Prisma Studio
```

